detailedDescription.articleBody: Tan Sri Dato' Seri Michelle Yeoh Choo-Kheng, better known by her stage name Michelle Yeoh, is a Malaysian actress who rose to fame with frequent roles in 1990s Hong Kong action films, and is best known internationally for her roles in the 1997 James Bond film Tomorrow Never Dies, and the Chinese-language martial arts film Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon.
